# Dawn
  `ending := "dawn"`
  > Morning arrives all at once. Rain lifts from Brindlewick as if someone has drawn back a curtain.
  > In the village square, every bell rope trembles though no bell is visible.
  > People step from doorways with cups in their hands and questions on their faces, blinking at a sky the color of clean linen.
  > `pool_offering` Somewhere nearby, a stranger laughs and flips a coin into the fountain. It lands without a splash.
  + -> [Visit the changed village](#.Aftermath)

## Aftermath
  > The woman with the blue scarf waits beside the dry fountain.
  > Her brass mirror is open on her palm, reflecting not the square but the pale shape of the vanished bell.
  + -> [Ask what happened](#.Explanation)
  + -> [Leave Brindlewick by the north road](#Epilogue)

### Explanation
  >> [Blue Scarf](/characters.saga#BlueScarf) You woke what was buried.
  >> That is not the same as saving it. But sometimes it is enough.
  >> Brindlewick will remember differently now. That may be mercy, or only another kind of bell.
  + -> [Continue](#..)

# Return
  `ending := "return"`
  > You wake at the table in the Hollow Bell inn. Rain taps against the shutters.
  > The letter is gone, but your palm is black with old key oil.
  > Downstairs, someone laughs at a joke you almost remember. The sound stops when you try to place it.
  + -> [Check what remains](#.Inventory)

## Inventory
  > You remember fragments: a tower, a pool, the shape of a bell inside an eye.
  > Your pockets are ordinary, but your hands feel as if they have carried something too heavy to keep.
  + `saw_hidden_name` -> [Whisper the hidden name](#Epilogue)
  + -> [Go back to sleep](#.Sleep)

### Sleep
  > You close your eyes and let the rain count the seconds.
  > It reaches thirteen, pauses, and begins again at one.
  - -> [By morning, the rain has washed every road clean.](end:)

# Epilogue
  > Brindlewick falls behind you. Somewhere under the road, something vast and hollow rings once.
  > The sound is gentle from this distance, almost kind, but every bird in the hedgerow rises at once.
  > `has_cloak` Your cloak snaps in the morning wind like a small, stubborn banner.
  - -> [The road carries you past Brindlewick, and the bell's final note follows you into the hills.](end:)
